=== 爭議 ===

2010年1月，未經審核的電影預告片段遭到家庭關懷組織的抨擊，認為[[克蘿伊·摩蕾茲|克蘿伊·摩蕾茲]]飾演{{link-en|超殺女|Hit-Girl}}的台詞：「來吧！你們這群娘砲！讓我看看你們有多屌！（臺譯）」對電影中僅僅11歲女孩而言過於暴力粗劣。家庭協會發言人約翰·莫里西（{{lang|en|John Morrissey}}）宣稱「（該片的）台詞太過不雅，且價值觀不當——完全沒有傳統超級英雄不見血勝利的可取之處。」<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/entertainment/sydney-confidential/family-outrage-at-film-kick-ass-violence-and-swearing/news-story/6f4f0640ce6ecf17b4928ac7752265bf |title=Family outrage at film Kick Ass (''sic'') violence and swearing |date=2010-01-13 |work=''The Daily Telegraph'' |accessdate=2018-01-19 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171207093525/https://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/entertainment/sydney-confidential/family-outrage-at-film-kick-ass-violence-and-swearing/news-story/6f4f0640ce6ecf17b4928ac7752265bf |archivedate=2017-12-07 |dead-url=no }}</ref>回應此爭議，摩蕾茲在訪談中表示，「如果我總是說《特攻聯盟》裡講的粗話，我可能整年都會被禁足！我將會被關在我房內直到20歲！我在未來幾萬年也絕對不會說那些髒話。我就是個一般，日復一日的普通女孩。」<ref>{{Cite web |title="Kick-Ass" star Chloe Moretz is One of 10 to Watch in 2010 |url=http://www.mtv.com/movies/news/articles/1630006/story.jhtml |accessdate=2018-01-19 |date=2010-01-20 |last=Carroll |first=Larry |work=MTV |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5vxkK8gTg?url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1630006/kickass-star-chloe-moretz-one-10-watch-2010.jhtml |archivedate=2011-01-23 |deadurl=no }}</ref>她也說，她的雙親都有看過該片的劇本，清楚其中的內容<ref>{{Cite web |title=Brad Pitt in London for Kick-Ass movie premiere |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/7500123/Brad-Pitt-in-London-for-Kick-Ass-movie-premiere.html |accessdate=2019-10-20 |date=2010-03-23 |work=''The Telegraph'' |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191020114549/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/7500123/Brad-Pitt-in-London-for-Kick-Ass-movie-premiere.html |archive-date=2019-10-20 }}</ref>。

摩蕾茲也表示，在拍片時，她不會讓自己直接說出電影的英文片名「Kick Ass」（直譯踢屁股，屬不文雅的話語），在訪談或公共場合她都說「該電影」，在家時則說「Kick-Butt」（意思一樣但比Kick Ass文雅）<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.scotsman.com/lifestyle/what-are-little-girls-made-of-sugar-and-spice-punches-and-the-odd-four-letter-word-when-they-re-the-surprise-star-of-kick-ass-1-796010 |title=What are little girls made of? Sugar and spice, punches and the odd four-letter word, when they're the surprise star of 'Kick-Ass' |last=Synnot |first=Siobhan |date=2010-03-24 |newspaper=''The Scotsman'' |accessdate=2018-01-19 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6waJX0tkK?url=https://www.scotsman.com/lifestyle/what-are-little-girls-made-of-sugar-and-spice-punches-and-the-odd-four-letter-word-when-they-re-the-surprise-star-of-kick-ass-1-796010 |archivedate=2018-01-19 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。另一演員{{link-en|克里斯多福·敏茲-普雷斯|Christopher Mintz-Plasse}}相當訝異大眾對台詞議題充滿爭議，卻忽略超殺女在電影中手刃眾多壞蛋的另一孩童暴力問題<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://e-edition.metroherald.ie/2010/04/14/ |title=Christopher Mintz-Passe: 60 Second interview |last=White |first=Lucy |date=2010-04-14 |newspaper=''Metro Herald'' |accessdate=2018-01-19 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110815091232/http://e-edition.metroherald.ie/2010/04/14/ |archivedate=2011-08-15 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。編劇之一{{link-en|珍·古德曼|Jane Goldman}}指出，「如果人們對超殺女的暴力行為感到震驚，很正常，但如果她說出C開頭的髒話，大家反而更震驚，那就顯得他們對不雅言語反應過度了。」<ref name="The Telegraph-Moretz" />

